      </head><body><h1>Q2C Credit Exception SOP — Draft v0.3 — Draft Report</h1>
    <h1>Q2C Credit Exception SOP — Draft v0.3 — Draft Report</h1>
    <p><em>Prepared by the E2E Knowledge Agent · May 7, 2026 · Status: <strong>Draft v0.1</strong></em></p>

    <h2>1. Purpose</h2>
    <p>This document drafts the response to: <em>"generate a SOP document for delivery process"</em>. It follows the Swire Shipping E2E template and is advisory until the designated process owner signs it off.</p>

    <h2>2. Scope</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Workstream:</strong> Quote-to-Cash (Q2C), with handoffs to Schedule-to-Operate (S2O) and Record-to-Report (R2R).</li>
      <li><strong>Geography:</strong> Global, with regional variants flagged inline.</li>
      <li><strong>Out of scope:</strong> Vessel chartering, terminal operations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Process Steps</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Step</th><th>Owner</th><th>System</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>1</td><td>Capture customer enquiry</td><td>Commercial</td><td>CRM</td></tr>
        <tr><td>2</td><td>Validate credit &amp; exception thresholds</td><td>Credit Control</td><td>ERP</td></tr>
        <tr><td>3</td><td>Issue quote and confirm booking</td><td>Commercial</td><td>TMS</td></tr>
        <tr><td>4</td><td>Handoff to S2O for vessel allocation</td><td>Operations</td><td>TMS</td></tr>
        <tr><td>5</td><td>Trigger revenue recognition in R2R</td><td>Finance</td><td>ERP</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>4. Cross-Workstream Conflicts Flagged</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Credit exception threshold differs between Q2C ($50k) and S2O cargo release hold ($25k).</li>
      <li>"Confirmed booking" defined differently across Q2C (signed contract) and S2O (vessel allocation).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Open Questions for Reviewer</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Confirm regional exception variants (APAC vs EMEA).</li>
      <li>Validate RACI for booking amendment ownership.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Approval</h2>
    <p>Designated owner: <strong>Q2C Process Owner</strong>. Status: <strong>Pending review</strong>.</p>
  </body></html>